Probabilistic Methods. 

The paper discusses the use of probabilistic models for change point and change curve modeling in stochastic processes and spatial statistics. The author uses Bayesian methods and Markov chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) algorithms to estimate parameters and make predictions. The paper also discusses the use of mixture models and model selection criteria based on likelihood and Bayesian information criteria. Overall, the paper focuses on probabilistic modeling and inference methods for analyzing data.
